### Test Categories Distribution Endpoint
### Prerequisites: You need a valid JWT token from a government user (officer/admin/super_admin)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api/v1
@token = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJlNDY5NjlmYS0zM2JiLTRhMzUtOTQ0Zi1lNmQ5NTdiZDJmYjciLCJyb2xlIjoiYWRtaW4iLCJuaXAiOiIxOTgwMDEwMTIwMDUwMTEwMDEiLCJhZ2VuY3lJZCI6IjAwMDAwMDAwLTAwMDAtMDAwMC0wMDAwLTAwMDAwMDAwMDAwMSIsImlhdCI6MTc3NjkxNzExNywiZXhwIjoxNzc2OTE4MDE3fQ.y2zPMk85xaqo0S4j4BW3acMJsFjWk1yfv56Si4NM4E8

### Test 1: Get categories distribution for 30 days (default)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/categories?period=30
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 2: Get categories distribution for 90 days
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/categories?period=90
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 3: Get categories distribution for 365 days
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/categories?period=365
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 4: Test without authentication (should fail with 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/categories?period=30

### Test 5: Test with invalid period (should use default 30)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/categories?period=invalid
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected Response Format:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "data": [
